manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Applicator free tampons for a more sustainable, plastic free choice. Just as natural as a period. Veeda Non-Applicator Tampons are made with ultra-absorbent all-natural 100% cotton for reliable, leak-proof protection. Designed with specialized grooves for added absorption and all-natural cotton string for easy removal. Available in: Lite, Regular, Super & Super Plus with Compact BPA-Free Applicator or Applicator Free Synthetic and/or scented period care products can irritate the sensitive skin of the vulva. Veeda tampons are natural, hypoallergenic and dermatologically tested, which is very important for women's health. In fact, statistics show that yeast infections are less likely to occur with natural products that contain no harsh chemicals and fragrances. Veeda tampons are made with naturally soft, absorbent 100% pure GMO-Free cotton (that’s it, nothing else!) ensuring that your body only meets with the purest, irritation free ingredients. Our 100% natural cotton is sourced directly from a global network of leading cotton traders and all cotton is cleansed with an oxygen cleansing process, not chlorine-bleached, for a healthier eco-friendlier product. This process removes all dirt and impurities including any synthetic matter and this is the exact same process by which all organic cotton is cleansed with, to ensure it also has no synthetic substances. This ensures that the final tampons are truly 100% natural cotton. Veeda tampons are lab-tested for over 250 harmful chemicals and contain no wood or synthetic fibres, no additives and no dioxins. Another advantage to using 100% pure, hypoallergenic cotton, is that cotton does not contribute to the growth of the bacteria that causes Toxic Shock Syndrome (TSS), irritation and allergic reactions.

Many of us are conscious of the ingredients in the foods we eat and the products we put on our skin and hair, choosing the hypoallergenic, organic or natural options. Yet, somehow, there is extremely low awareness among women of what ingredients are used in their sanitary protection products and what implications they may have for their health. We believe that natural products are better for you and for our planet. We also believe that when it comes to products that touch the skin, particularly in the most intimate parts of the body, it’s important to know exactly where it came from and how it got there. This is why we are committed to ensuring that all of our products contain ONLY pure, hypoallergenic, 100% natural cotton with No Nasty Chemicals and No Dyes. Unlike other brands, our cotton is grown naturally, not manufactured or altered. Plus, all our products are gently cleansed with oxygen and are chlorine-free. Conventional period care products from well-known brands can be made from blends of bleached cotton and/or synthetic products. They can also contain dioxins from the bleaching process, herbicide residues, synthetic chemicals, artificial fragrances, and dyes. We want to make sure that our products are kinder to the earth in every way possible. After learning how conventionally made feminine care products affected our body and environment, Veeda was created. The average woman uses 11,000 feminine care products in her lifetime; this fact alone keeps us inspired to create a top of line sustainable process when manufacturing our products. Veeda products are made with pure, hypoallergenic, 100% natural cotton. Our cotton is grown naturally, not manufactured or altered. Both our tampons and pads are gently cleansed with oxygen and are chlorine-free. Veeda tampons are made only with 100% Natural Cotton and have No Nasty Chemicals, No Synthetics, and No Dyes. Knowing the facts, consider making a better choice by making Veeda your go-to natural period care brand.
ABOUT VEEDA We created Veeda because you and your body deserve the best. No harsh chemicals here — just natural goodness that always goes with the flow (literally).

Better for You No Chemicals. No Synthetics. No Dyes. Our applicator-free tampons are 100% natural GMO-free cotton and hypoallergenic. Natural leak-free protection you can count on! Better for the planet Our tampons are packaged using recyclable materials. Veeda is committed to sustainably-sourced ingredients and safe manufacturing processes. Better for all We’re working to end period poverty once and for all. Every time you buy a Veeda product, you help us deliver period care essentials to those who need them the most.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Follow the Red Line!
reviews.reviewText: I love how simple and easy these are for travel! If you are comfortable not using an applicator then I absolutely recommend this product!! Overall decent absorption rate and shape upon expansion, so if you want to try something new and get the most bang for your buck, look no further! 😁

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Surprised! This was and amazing product and will buy again.
reviews.reviewText: I was surprised how comfortable and absorbent this product was especially for the price. I was trying to find something that was more natural as other products have started to irritate me. Was a bit uncomfortable about not having an applicator but that wasn't an issue once I began to use it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars good tampons, not as absorbent as others but still really good
reviews.reviewText: It is so good for my cramps to use natural products, and it helps so much. I like these ones, and they are really good for their price. Sometimes with more expensive ones I have found slightly better absorbancy and less likely to get overflow leakage, but it's not much and worth it for the price and how my body feels using these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I keep a few of these in all my bags and I love how small and discreet they are. Surprised how hard it is to find good tampons w/o an applicator but these fit the bill!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great organic item for the price!
reviews.reviewText: Have been using Cora, which I love, but these are a bit cheaper and seem to work as well. Only issue is they don’t have “mixed sizes” boxes like Cora. I’ll probably switch off and use these on lighter days.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So glad to be able to get these without the applicator!
reviews.reviewText: Veeda tampons are my favorite. I find other tampons (even “natural” ones) irritating, but I’ve never had that problem with Veeda. I just had previously only seen them with a wasteful plastic applicator. I’m so glad to be able to buy them without an applicator. They can be discreetly carried in a change purse or pocket, and only a small amount of plastic wrapper for waste. The absorbency is equivalent to Cora or OB applicator free tampons.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: First, my problem I didn't read there was no applicator. Not enjoying the thought of putting it in without the applicator. The next part the wrapper on the outside took about a minute or two to get off. Nothing like struggling with the wrapper in a public restroom.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: They didn’t come in the proper packaging. Not only are they quite large and inconvenient boxes, but it isn’t the proper packaging which seems sketchy to me. I bought these for the compact and convenient size/packaging. And now I don’t have that but also I feel uncomfortable using them since the packaging is sketch. Are these genuine Veeda? I don’t know. I don’t appreciate false advertising. The pictures show it in the proper package.
Love these, gonna order more for sure

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on May 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The product is great compared to toxic and bleached alternatives. High-quality product and great outer packaging.The tampons are however individually wrapped in plastic - Not great for sustainability or keeping endocrine disruptors out of your body. I also noted that the tampons expand only in diameter rather than width to better suit the body shape which can cause leakage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I assumed these were the same size to the OBs super, shock on me. Will keep them but recommend checking size before ordering
I love that there is no applicator! It’s so hard finding tampons without. Plastic is a little tough to take off.
doesn't shred apart like some natural products do. Easy to use, very comfortable
